Intro

Hi! I’m a PhD student in the Shallow Water Earth Observation Lab at the University of Ottawa. I study atmospheric correction for satellite-based aquatic remote sensing over coastal areas.

Links

CV
LinkedIn

Modelling and Correcting for the Adjacency Effect

My PhD thesis focuses on the adjacency effect and how it affects water’s TOA radiance; I model this with 3D Monte Carlo radiative-transfer (RT) simulations. This work will support satellite-derived bathymetry and remote sensing (RS) of biochemical processes in coastal areas.
